DVWA & OWASP Juice Shop

Description:
These applications provide a lightweight, safe playground for learning web-app security, testing scanners, and practicing exploitation techniques. Includes Damn Vulnerable Web App (DVWA) and OWASP Juice Shop. For training only — never expose these to production or the public internet.

What’s included

DVWA — classic PHP/MySQL vulnerable app for learning common web flaws (SQLi, XSS, CSRF, file upload, etc.).
OWASP Juice Shop — modern intentionally vulnerable Node.js app that covers a broad range of vulnerabilities and challenge-based learning.


Quick start

DVWA
1. Clone these repos:
  -  git clone https://github.com/digininja/DVWA.git
  - cd /var/www/html
    - here you should see the DVWA directory listed
    -try navigating to http://localhost, you should be greeted by a page not discovered page, this is because by default the apache server in which DVWA runs on has not been started. 
-run sudo service apache2 start
  - renavigate back to http://localhost, and you should see the following page. Ensure to use http and not https as it will cause issues
-if you try to navigate to the source folder of DVWA, you should be greeted by a error message reagrding the config file needing to to copied to another file, run the following:
  - cd /var/www/html/DVWA 
  - cp config/config.inc.php.dist config/config.inc.php
  - service mariadb start 


Juice-Shop
1. Clone these repos:
  -  git clone https://github.com/juice-shop/juice-shop.gitkali
2. run the follow commands:
  - cd juiceshop
  - sudo npm install
  - sudo npm start 

